cardano-node
------------

Systemd services are installed as a template, and instances are named by the network.

For example, to run mainnet:

    systemctl enable --now cardano-node@mainnet.service

To run a testnet, use the corresponding network instance:

    systemctl enable --now cardano-node@preview.service

Supported networks are 'mainnet', 'preview' and 'preprod'
